DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
      "PGstandard.pl",
      "MathObjects.pl",
      "answerHints.pl",
      "PGML.pl",
      "PCCmacros.pl",
      "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################
    
Context("Numeric");
Context()->flags->set(reduceConstants=>0, reduceConstantFunctions=>0, formatStudentAnswer=>parsed);
Context()->noreduce('(-x)-y','(-x)+y');

Context()->variables->add(i=>'Real');

$a = random(-1,1,2)*random(2,12,1);

$ans = Compute("-$a*i")->reduce;

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_PGML

Rewrite the following expression into the form of a+b[`i`]:

     [`` \frac{[$a]}{i} = ``][___________]{$ans}

END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

By definition, [`i=\sqrt{-1}`], so we have [`i^{2}=-1`].

To get rid of *[`i`]* in the denominator, we do.

    [`` 
\begin{aligned}
   &\phantom{{}=} \frac{[$a]}{i} \\
   &= \frac{[$a]\cdot i}{i \cdot i} \\
   &= \frac{[$a] i}{i^{2}} \\
   &= \frac{[$a] i}{-1} \\
   &= [$ans]
\end{aligned}
    ``]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

